OL,4,Cin almost a quarter of hate crime
OL,5,Creports
OL,7,FThe Tories opposed the legislation
OL,8,Fwhile it was going through Parliament
OL,9,Fand have spoken out about its impact
OL,10,Fon "overstretched" police, as well as
OL,11,Fraising concerns about freedom of
OL,12,Fspeech.
OL,14,FMr Ross said: "We said at the very
OL,15,Fbeginning this Act would put free
OL,16,Fspeech at risk."
