OL,5,Creports
OL,7,FMr Yousaf hit out at the Tories ` who
OL,8,Flost a vote in Holyrood on Wednesday
OL,9,Fcalling for the Act to be repealed `
OL,10,Fsaying: "If the Hate Crime Act didn't
OL,11,Fexist, with the stroke of a pen it
OL,12,Fwould have removed protection against
OL,13,Fstirring up hatred for those who
OL,14,Fsuffer racist abuse, for those who
OL,15,Fsuffer antisemitism, for those who
OL,16,Fsuffer Islamophobia, for those who
OL,17,Fsuffer homophobia, transphobia, those
OL,18,Fwho suffer abuse because of their
OL,19,Fdisability."
